1. The game is created
2. The game is initialized
2.1. For every player 4 figures are placed in their houses
2.2. The field is generated, for every player a street is made out of about 12 spots which may contain figures
2.3. The homes are generated which again contain 4 spots which are to be moved to
3. The game starts and the state is changed to runnig.
3.1 While the game is running:
3.1.1 Has the game been finished, is it over?
3.1.2 End the game or continue
3.1.3 What player is at turn?
3.1.4 Let that player do his turn.
3.1.4.1 Has that player have had a figure in the field?
3.1.4.1.1 Let that player try to get a figure out of his home.
3.1.4.1.2 Let that player move one of his figures.
3.1.4.1.2.1 The figure moves according to the die rolled.
3.1.4.1.2.2 The figure may kick another figure.
3.1.4.1.2.3 The figure may enter the players home.
3.1.4.1.2.4 End that players turn.
3.1.5 Let the next player do his turn.
3.2 The game ends. It get set to the game over state
3.3 Ask for new game.
3.4 The game may start over.
4. Show credits, or don't.



